  "prompt": "Does money laundering fall under criminal legislation?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is considered a criminal offense under both national and international legislation. Most countries have specific laws criminalizing money laundering as part of their efforts to combat financial crime. These laws typically:\n\n1. Define money laundering as a criminal activity\n2. Establish penalties including fines and imprisonment\n3. Require financial institutions to report suspicious transactions\n4. Provide legal frameworks for investigating and prosecuting money laundering cases\n\nIn many jurisdictions, money laundering is treated as a serious financial crime with significant legal consequences.",
